01/12/2003
BJELOVAR, Croatia -- The Croatian Farmer's Party (HSS) is expected to decide Monday (1 December) or Tuesday about participation in a coalition government with the Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ). HSS leader Zlatko Tomcic said Sunday he had heard from most of the party's regional units about possible co-operation with the election winner HDZ. Smaller centrist formations are also expected to back a coalition government led by HDZ.
Also Sunday, Croatian physicians launched an AIDS prevention campaign, on the eve of World Aids Day. According to official statistics, Croatia has one of the lowest rates of HIV infection in the world. (HINA - 30/11/03; HINA - 29/11/03)
